Question 1

Use R package UScensus2010county to complete the following tasks: (20 pt.)

Question 1(a)

Plot a map of New York counties using the qtm function.

qtm(shp.1a)

How many counties in New York State?

Question 1(d)

Whats the 3-digit fips code of Broome County?

broome.fips <- df.1[df.1$NAME10 == "Broome",]$county

Question 3(c)

Aggregate all bands to generate a mean NDVI raster and a maximum NDVI raster; save the two new raster datasets to the hard drive.

ndvi.rb <- brick("NDVI.nc")
ndvi.mean <- calc(ndvi.rb, fun = mean)
plot(ndvi.mean)

writeRaster(ndvi.mean, filename = "mean_ndvi", overwrite = TRUE)
ndvi.max <- calc(ndvi.rb, fun = max)
plot(ndvi.max)

writeRaster(ndvi.mean, filename = "max_ndvi", overwrite = TRUE)
